A3: Incarceration

Introduction

In the US black and brown folks are disproportionally incarcerated at a much higher rate than their white counterparts. This has to do with a lack of a fair trial and questionable policing. I will be analyzing the year to see any trends. I will also analyze population rates from all races to see if any racial disparity arise.

The Dataset

Who collected the data? The data was collected by the Vera Institute for Justice. How was the data collected or generated? The data was collected by merging data they found with original jail sets in order to examine both jail and prison incarceration.

Why was the data collected? This data was collected to see demographic disparities that arise and any relevant trends. There is divided justice in the US therefore it is important to study that as well. How many observations (rows) are in your data?

Some possible limitations are problems with this data is that there are a lot of null values in the table.
